        "In 2005, USAID under PEPFAR established the Supply Chain Management System (SCMS) to provide a reliable, cost-effective, and secure supply of products for HIV/AIDS programs in PEPFAR-supported countries. This is basically a supply chain management system project and dataset provides an in-depth look at their logistics processes, capturing important information on purchase orders (POs), shipment methods, vendor agreements (INCO terms), delivery schedules, and product-specific details such as item descriptions and dosage forms.\n",
        "\n",
        "Given the rise of eCommerce and global distribution, companies like FedEx must continuously optimize their logistics operations to maintain a competitive edge. The projectâ€™s goal with solution that might help scale-up and streamline supply chain operations, improving delivery timelines and reducing costs that might enable real and lasting progress towards achieving universal access by bringing down the cost of treatment and strengthening in-country supply chains.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "The dataset is designed to provide insights into how shipments are managed, identify bottlenecks or delays, and ensure cost-effectiveness. By analyzing the data, . Cost savings are being leveraged to increase the funding available to treat more patients."
