        "## ***2. Understanding Your Variables***"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nA9Y7ga8ng1Z"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Dataset Columns\n",
        "fed_df.columns"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "j7xfkqrt5Ag5",
        "collapsed": true
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Dataset Describe\n",
        "fed_df.info()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DnOaZdaE5Q5t",
        "collapsed": true
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Data Description**\n",
        "1. **ID** - identity number\n",
        "2. **Project Code** - Project code for the shipment\n",
        "3. **PQ #** - Price quote (PQ) number\n",
        "4. **PO / SO #** - Price Order / Sales Order --- PO is a buyer's request to a seller (supplier) to order the goods/services\n",
        "5. **ASN/DN #** - Shipment number: Advanced Shipment Note (ASN) for Direct Drop deliveries, or Delivery Note (DN) for from RDC deliveries\n",
        "6. **Country** - Destination country , where shipment is to be delivered\n",
        "7. **Managed By** - SCMS managing office: either the Program Management Office (PMO) in the U.S. or the relevant SCMS field office\n",
        "8. **Fulfill Via** - Method through which the shipment was fulfilled: via Direct Drop from vendor or from stock available in the RDCs( retail distribution centers )\n",
        "9. **Vendor INCO Term** - The vendor INCO term (also known as International Commercial Terms) for Direct Drop deliveries---a set of 11 internationally recognized rules which define the responsibilities of sellers and buyers. Incoterms specifies who is responsible for paying for and managing the shipment, insurance, documentation, customs clearance, and other logistical activities.\n",
        "10. ***Shipment Mode*** - Method by which commodities are shipped\n",
        "11. **PQ First Sent to Client Date** - Date the PQ is first sent to the client\n",
        "12. **PO Sent to Vendor Date** - Date the PO is first sent to the vendor\n",
        "13. **Scheduled Delivery Date** - Date on which delivery to client was recorded in SCMS information systems\n",
        "14. **Product Group** - Product group for item, i.e. ARV, HRDT\n",
        "15. **Sub Classification** - Identifies relevant product sub classifications, such as whether ARVs are pediatric or adult, whether a malaria product is an artemisinin-based combination therapy (ACT), etc.\n",
        "16. **Vendor** - Vendor name\n",
        "17. **Item Description** - Product name and formulation from Partnership for Supply Chain Management (PFSCM) Item Master\n",
        "18. **Molecule/Test Type** - Active drug(s) or test kit type\n",
        "19. **Brand** - Generic or branded name for the item\n",
        "20. **Dosage** - Item dosage and unit\n",
        "21. **Dosage Form** - Dosage form for the item (tablet, oral solution, injection, etc.).\n",
        "22. **Unit of Measure (Per Pack)** - Pack quantity (pills or test kits) used to compute unit price\n",
        "23. **Line Item Quantity** - Total quantity (packs) of commodity per line item\n",
        "24. **Line Item Value** - Total value of commodity per line itemÂ¶\n",
        "25. **Pack Price** - Cost per pack (i.e. month s supply of ARVs, pack of 60 test kits)\n",
        "26. **Unit Price** - Cost per pill (for drugs) or per test (for test kits)\n",
        "27. **Manufacturing Site** - Identifies manufacturing site for the line item for direct drop and from RDC deliveries\n",
        "28. **First Line Designation** - Designates if the line in question shows the aggregated freight costs and weight associated with all items on the ASN DN\n",
        "29. **Weight (Kilograms)** - Weight for all lines on an ASN DN\n",
        "30. **Freight Cost (USD)** - Freight charges associated with all lines on the respective ASN DN\n",
        "31. **Line Item Insurance (USD)** - Line item cost of insurance, created by applying an annual flat rate ( ) to commodity cost\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "JkYljuI6q0ma"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 3. **Data Wrangling**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "v5iZvpQSA7ur"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#converting the date columns to the proper datetime data type\n",
        "fed_df['Scheduled Delivery Date']= pd.to_datetime(fed_df['Scheduled Delivery Date'],format='%d-%b-%y')\n",
        "fed_df['Delivery Recorded Date'] = pd.to_datetime(fed_df['Delivery Recorded Date'],format='%d-%b-%y')\n",
        "fed_df['PQ First Sent to Client Date'] = pd.to_datetime(fed_df['PQ First Sent to Client Date'], format='%d-%b-%y',errors='coerce')\n",
        "fed_df['PO Sent to Vendor Date'] = pd.to_datetime(fed_df['PO Sent to Vendor Date'], format='%d-%b-%y',errors='coerce')\n",
