      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "| Chart | Best For | Insight Gained |\n",
        "| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
        "| **Bar Chart** | Ranking, absolute values, comparison of magnitude. | \"South Africa has **212 more** shipments than Nigeria.\" |\n",
        "| **Pie Chart** | Proportions, market share, total distribution. | \"The top 8 countries account for over **$75\\%$** of all shipments.\" |\n",
        "\n",
        "***\n",
        "\n",
        "## ðŸ’¡ Insights from the Charts\n",
        "\n",
        "The visualizations illustrates Top 16 Countries by Shipment Count and by \"Shipment Distribution.\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Concentration and Dominance (Pie Chart & Bar Chart)**\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Top 3 Drivers:** The market is heavily concentrated, with the **top three countries**â€”**South Africa (13.6%), Nigeria (11.6%), and CÃ´te d'Ivoire (10.5%)**â€”accounting for **35.7%** of the total shipments.\n",
        "* **High Market Share:** The **top 8 individual countries** (South Africa through Haiti) collectively account for over **$75\\%$** of the total global shipments (the sum of percentages from 13.6% down to 6.3%).\n",
        "* **Long Tail is Small:** The collection of all the smaller countries (those with 100 or fewer shipments) combined into the **\"Other Countries\"** category accounts for only **6.4%** of the total shipments, confirming that the vast majority of resources and volume are handled by the large individual countries listed.\n",
        "\n",
        "### **Ranking and Magnitude (Bar Chart)**\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Clear Leader:** **South Africa** is the undisputed leader with **1,406** shipments, a significant margin ahead of the next country.\n",
        "* **Close Competitors:** **Nigeria (1,194)** and **CÃ´te d'Ivoire (1,083)** are close contenders for the top spot.\n",
        "* **Drop-off:** There is a notable drop in volume after the top three, as the fourth country, Uganda, has 779 shipments, which is approximately **$28\\%$ less** than CÃ´te d'Ivoire.\n",
        "\n",
