        "that isolates the manufacturing origin, showing a significant concentration of sourcing in one country.**\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "**Dedicated Logistics Corridor:** The high volume justifies the creation of a dedicated, highly optimized logistics corridor out of India. Resources should be focused on maximizing efficiency from Indian ports and airports.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Infrastructure Investment:** Logistics planning must focus heavily on securing long-term capacity and favorable rates for outbound air and ocean freight from major Indian hubs (like Mumbai/Nhava Sheva or Delhi).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Air Freight Dependency:** Given the previous analysis showed a heavy reliance on Air Freight for essential drugs (ARV/HRDT), this means the vast majority of global air freight volume originates in India. This necessitates:\n",
        "  *   Securing charter capacity or long-term block space agreements with air carriers.\n",
        "  *   Developing robust cold chain infrastructure at the Indian manufacturing sites and departure airports."
