        "**A Heatmap** is a graphical representation of data where the individual values contained in a matrix are represented as colors. It excels at revealing patterns, high/low values, and anomalies in complex, multi-variable data.\n",
        "\n",
        "**1. Two-Dimensional Comparison (Matrix View)**\n",
        "The Problem: Your data is structured as a matrix (or pivot table) where the row variable (Product Group) interacts with the column variable (Shipment Mode).\n",
        "\n",
        "**2. Instant Pattern Recognition (Color Scale)**\n",
        "The Benefit: By using a color gradient (e.g., darker color = higher cost), the human eye can instantly spot the most critical combinations without needing to read every number."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8agQvks0phqQ"
      }
