        "Based on the provided heatmaps and code, here is a professional write-up analyzing the logistical efficiency and cost drivers within the SCMS dataset.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### **CHART 15: Logistics Efficiency & Mode Optimization Matrix**\n",
        "\n",
        "This analysis utilizes two cross-referenced heatmaps to evaluate the relationship between physical **Weight (kg)** and financial **Freight Cost (USD)** across different product categories and transport modes.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### **1. ARV Logistics: The \"Bulk Powerhouse\"**\n",
        "\n",
        "Antiretrovirals (ARVs) represent the most significant operational volume in the system.\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Weight Dominance**: ARVs exhibit the highest average weights across nearly all major modes, with **Air Charter (6,951.48 kg)**, **Ocean (6,912.99 kg)**, and **Truck (6,625.83 kg)** showing nearly identical high-volume profiles.\n",
        "* **Cost Efficiency**: While **Air Charter** for ARVs is expensive in absolute terms ($21,052.14), it is moving the largest physical mass.\n",
        "* **The Ocean Advantage**: Interestingly, the average weight for ARV via **Ocean (6,912.99 kg)** is almost the same as Air Charter, but the cost drops significantly to **$12,610.54**.\n",
        "* **Business Insight**: This confirms that shifting ARV volume from Air Charter to Ocean provides massive cost savings (approx. 40%) while maintaining the same bulk delivery capacity.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### **2. HRDT Strategy: High Cost, Moderate Weight**\n",
        "\n",
        "High-Risk Diagnostic Tests (HRDT) show a distinct logistical profile compared to medications.\n",
        "\n",
        "* **The Ocean Penalty**: HRDT has the highest single average freight cost in the entire matrix: **$24,129.05 for Ocean shipments**.\n",
        "* **Weight Discrepancy**: Despite having the highest cost, the average weight for HRDT via Ocean is only **3,566.67 kg**â€”nearly half the weight of an ARV shipment that costs $11,000 less.\n",
        "* **Business Insight**: This indicates that HRDT shipments via Ocean are likely subject to specialized requirementsâ€”such as **Cold Chain infrastructure** or hazardous material handlingâ€”that drive prices up regardless of weight.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### **3. Standard Air: The \"Emergency Valve\"**\n",
        "\n",
        "Standard Air is used consistently across all product groups (ACT, ANTM, ARV, HRDT, MRDT) but with much lower physical profiles.\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Low Weight, High Premium**: Across all groups, Air weights are relatively low (e.g., **946.46 kg for ACT**), yet costs remain significant (e.g., **$8,759.20 for ACT**).\n",
        "* **Business Insight**: Standard Air serves as the \"contingency\" mode. It is utilized for smaller, time-sensitive batches where speed is prioritized over the cost-per-kilogram efficiency seen in Charter or Ocean modes.\n",
