    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**1.Bar Chart (Simple):** A simple Bar Chart (or Column Chart) is used to compare the magnitude of individual, independent categories and is Best For Showing the ranking and scale difference between groups.\n",
        "\n",
        "  * **Purpose**: Comparison of costs\n",
        "  * **Metric**: A single total value (mean cost per item ) for each category.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "**2.Stacked Bar Chart:** A Stacked Bar Chart is used to compare the composition of a total across different categories and is Best For Showing how parts contribute to a whole and how that composition changes across different groups.\n",
        "\n",
        "  * **Purpose**: Compositional Analysis\n",
        "  * **Metric**: The total of a value, broken down into its components, across categories.\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-vsMzt_np1ck"
      }
