    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Cost Efficiency Analysis by Shipment Mode\n",
        "The analysis uses the **Cost Per Dollar of Value** (`cost_per_dollar`) metric to determine which transport mode offers the best value. This metric is calculated as: $\\frac{\\text{Freight Cost} + \\text{Insurance}}{\\text{Line Item Value}}$.\n",
        "\n",
        "| Rank | Shipment Mode | Total Item Value (USD) | Cost Per Dollar of Value | Logistical Role |\n",
        "| :---: | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
        "| **1** | **Ocean** | \\$340,102.27 | **\\$0.0391** | **Most Cost-Efficient** |\n",
        "| **2** | **Truck** | \\$207,555.61 | **\\$0.0504** | Efficient Regional/Ground Transport |\n",
        "| **3** | **Air Charter** | \\$379,034.20 | **\\$0.0570** | High-Volume, Exclusive Air Service |\n",
        "| **4** | **Air (Standard)** | \\$102,615.07 | **\\$0.1035** | Least Cost-Efficient |\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### 1. Most Cost-Efficient Mode: Ocean Freight ðŸš¢\n",
        "**Ocean freight** is the clear winner in cost efficiency, delivering the lowest **Cost Per Dollar of Value at \\$0.0391**.\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Role:** Ocean is highly efficient due to its high capacity and long transit times, making it ideal for **bulk commodities** (like the ACT drug) and **non-time-critical products** where cost minimization is the primary objective.\n",
        "* **Strategy:** This mode should be maximized for planned, long-term procurement of stable-demand items to capture maximum savings.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 2. Standard Air vs. Air Charter (High-Cost Modes) âœˆï¸\n",
        "\n",
        "The two air modes show a significant cost trade-off between standard service and dedicated capacity.\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Standard Air (Least Efficient):** With a Cost Per Dollar of **\\$0.1035**, standard scheduled air freight is the **most expensive transport mode**. This high cost is likely due to low volume per shipment (avg. value of \\$102k) combined with premium freight rates for speed, making it inefficient unless the demand is extremely urgent or low-volume.\n",
        "* **Air Charter (Efficient for Scale):** Air Charter is surprisingly the **third most efficient** mode at **\\$0.0570** per dollar, demonstrating a massive **45% cost improvement** over standard Air.\n",
        "    * **Role:** This suggests that when the organization needs to move large, consolidated volumes quickly (avg. value of \\$379kâ€”the highest among all modes), leveraging a dedicated charter dramatically reduces the per-unit cost by buying capacity in bulk.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3. Truck Freight (Ground Efficiency) ðŸš›\n",
        "\n",
        "**Truck freight** is the second most cost-effective mode at **\\$0.0504** per dollar.\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Role:** This mode serves as an efficient ground link, likely handling domestic or regional transport and last-mile distribution. Its cost efficiency is better than either air mode, making it the preferred choice for **time-sensitive land transport**.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ZYdMsrqVp1ck"
